title.rendered: Hyderabad vs Rajasthan, Indian T20 League 2023: Today’s Fantasy Team Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report & Fantasy Tips

content.rendered:
Fantasy Team for Hyderabad vs Rajasthan Match

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Heinrich Klaasen, Aiden Markram, and Marco Jansen will not be available for this game.

Hyderabad: Mayank Agarwal, Abhishek Sharma, Rahul Tripathi, Harry Brook*, Glenn Phillips* (wk), Abdul Samad, Washington Sundar, Bhuvneshwar Kumar (c), Adil Rashid*, Umran Malik, Fazalhaq Farooqi*

Rajasthan: Jos Buttler*, Yashaswi Jaiswal, Devdutt Padikkal, Sanju Samson (c & wk), Shimron Hetmyer*, Riyan Parag, Jason Holder*, Ravichandran Ashwin, Trent Boult*, Kuldeep Sen, Yuzvendra Chahal

Pitch Report

Venue: Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium, Hyderabad

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 181

2nd innings average score: 187

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Good for batting

Wins

Batting 1st: 33%

Batting 2nd: 67%

Also Read:

Delhi vs Gujarat Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day

Over the years, Sanju Samson has been a thorn in Hyderabad’s flesh, accumulating 670 runs at 45. 

Bhuvneshwar Kumar has bagged 37 wickets, including the best figures of five for 19 at the Rajiv Gandhi International Stadium. Against Rajasthan, he has 14 wickets.

Although Jos Buttler averages 23 versus Rajasthan, one cannot overlook his overall impact in the tournament. He averages 40 with the bat and has pouched 43 catches.

Yuzvendra Chahal has taken 20 wickets against Hyderabad – of which 19 have come in a night game. Above all, he has taken the most wickets (56) by an Indian since 2022 in competitive T20s.

Umran Malik picked the most wickets (22), including one five-for and a four-for in 2022, at an impressive strike rate of 13.41.

Besides adding 259 runs at 37, Abhishek Sharma took 10 wickets in the 2022-23 T20 domestic season. His ability to open the batting and bowling aids his selection percentage in fantasy leagues.

In the same tournament, Riyan Parag collected 253 runs at 63. Moreover, he is a safe fielder in the deep, generating handy points by pouching 17 catches – the joint-most in the previous edition of the Indian T20 League.

Adil Rashid has gone wicketless only once this year in franchise cricket, scalping 14 wickets in the process.

Fazalhaq Farooqi produced bonus points for a three-for thrice in his last 10 professional T20s, overall taking 16 wickets.

35 wickets have fallen at the venue in the last three games – of which 17 belonged to pacers and 14 to spinners.
